    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b6d27219_72aa2603",
        "filename": "client/downloader/downloader.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 80,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000487
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-04T15:26:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If this one and FetchFile are non blocking, maybe the name should be changed to something that hints this is async, e.g. EnqueueXXX, FetchAsync or something like that. In particular there\u0027s no way to know when it completed for the caller.\n\nThe more I think about it, the more I think I\u0027d prefer it to be sync (but I\u0027m not strongly for, so feel free to push back).\n\nIn the case of https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/client/archiver#Archiver.Push I decided to return a token because I needed the client to know at which stage the item is, to be able to have https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/client/archiver#Item.WaitForHashed. This is important as this permits efficient hashing (and caching of thereof) in the pipeline. This is not needed for download.",
      "revId": "202af8115b472ffaa293a9c0ac0f42a4fad8fa2e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8fb3f0ef_41339a0e",
        "filename": "client/downloader/downloader.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 80,
      "author": {
        "id": 1154295
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-04T19:58:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not strongly for async either, my only concern was future use-cases where maybe you want to download many isolated trees or files at a time. Then you don\u0027t need to roll your own work pool on top of the sync calls. The only use-case that comes to mind is maybe downloading many files in parallel, outside of an isolated tree (which would need a work pool anyway, so I figured why not just have isolated trees and files share the pool, the implementation becomes a bit cleaner that way).\n\nIf I do make these calls sync, then I\u0027d like to ask whether I should just spin up the pool specially for FetchIsolated? Since FetchFile doesn\u0027t need anything special.",
      "parentUuid": "b6d27219_72aa2603",
      "revId": "202af8115b472ffaa293a9c0ac0f42a4fad8fa2e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
